Sentencas: The need for reducing the operating temperature of solid-oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) imposed by cost reduction has pushed significant progress in fundamental understanding of the individual components, as well as materials innovation and device engineering.
Titulo: Low-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells based on proton-conducting electrolytes

Sentencas: Proton-conducting oxides have emerged as potential alternative electrolyte materials to oxygen-ion conducting oxides for operation at low and intermediate temperatures.
Titulo: Low-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells based on proton-conducting electrolytes

Sentencas: This article describes major recent developments in electrolytes, electrodes, and complete fuel cell performance for SOFCs based on proton-conducting electrolytes.
Titulo: Low-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells based on proton-conducting electrolytes

Sentencas: Although the performance of such fuel cells is still relatively modest, significant improvements in the power density output have been made during the last couple of years, and this trend is expected to continue.
Titulo: Low-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells based on proton-conducting electrolytes
